# 🚨 CRITICAL IMPLEMENTATION ISSUES FOUND

## Issues That Must Be Fixed

### 1. Missing @ApiOperation Decorators
**ALL controller endpoints are missing @ApiOperation decorators!**

❌ **Current Implementation:**
```ts
@Get(':id')
@Auth([RoleType.USER])
@HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)
@ApiUUIDParam('id')
@ApiResponse({
  status: HttpStatus.OK,
  description: 'Get users list',
  type: UserDto,
})
getUser(@UUIDParam('id') userId: Uuid): Promise<UserDto> {
  return this.userService.getUser(userId);
}
```

✅ **Required Implementation:**
```ts
@Get(':id')
@Auth([RoleType.USER])
@HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)
@ApiOperation({
  summary: 'Get user by ID',
  description: 'Retrieves a specific user by their unique identifier. Requires user authentication and returns complete user profile data.'
})
@ApiUUIDParam('id')
@ApiOkResponse({ type: UserDto })
getUser(@UUIDParam('id') userId: Uuid): Promise<UserDto> {
  return this.userService.getUser(userId);
}
```

### 2. Entity Ownership Violation
**PostEntity imports UserEntity from another module - VIOLATION of entity ownership rules!**

❌ **Current Implementation:**
```ts
// src/modules/post/post.entity.ts
import { UserEntity } from '../user/user.entity.ts'; // ❌ WRONG!

@Entity({ name: 'posts' })
export class PostEntity extends AbstractEntity<PostDto> {
  @ManyToOne(() => UserEntity, (userEntity) => userEntity.posts)
  user!: Relation<UserEntity>; // ❌ Cross-module entity usage
}
```

✅ **Required Implementation:**
```ts
// src/modules/post/post.entity.ts
// Remove UserEntity import and relationship
// Use UserService for cross-module communication instead

@Entity({ name: 'posts' })
export class PostEntity extends AbstractEntity<PostDto> {
  @Column({ type: 'uuid' })
  userId!: Uuid; // ✅ Keep only the foreign key
  
  // Remove direct entity relationship
}
```

### 3. CQRS Handler Return Types
**Command handlers missing explicit return types**

❌ **Current Implementation:**
```ts
@CommandHandler(CreatePostCommand)
export class CreatePostHandler implements ICommandHandler<CreatePostCommand, PostEntity> {
  async execute(command: CreatePostCommand) { // ❌ Missing return type
    // ...
  }
}
```

✅ **Required Implementation:**
```ts
@CommandHandler(CreatePostCommand)
export class CreatePostHandler implements ICommandHandler<CreatePostCommand, PostEntity> {
  async execute(command: CreatePostCommand): Promise<PostEntity> { // ✅ Explicit return type
    // ...
  }
}
```

### 4. Inconsistent API Response Types
**Using generic @ApiResponse instead of specific response decorators**

❌ **Current Implementation:**
```ts
@ApiResponse({
  status: HttpStatus.OK,
  description: 'Get users list',
  type: UserDto,
})
```

✅ **Required Implementation:**
```ts
@ApiOkResponse({ type: UserDto })
// or
@ApiCreatedResponse({ type: UserDto })
// or  
@ApiAcceptedResponse()
```

### 5. Service Method Inconsistencies
**PostService.updatePost has a bug - saving updatePostDto instead of postEntity**

❌ **Current Implementation:**
```ts
async updatePost(id: Uuid, updatePostDto: UpdatePostDto): Promise<void> {
  // ...
  this.postRepository.merge(postEntity, updatePostDto);
  await this.postRepository.save(updatePostDto); // ❌ WRONG! Should save postEntity
}
```

✅ **Required Implementation:**
```ts
async updatePost(id: Uuid, updatePostDto: UpdatePostDto): Promise<void> {
  // ...
  this.postRepository.merge(postEntity, updatePostDto);
  await this.postRepository.save(postEntity); // ✅ CORRECT!
}
```

